'''Robert Sheriff Black''' (1868 – 4 January 1939) was [[Mayor of Dunedin]] from 1929 to 1933. 

==Biography==
Black was born in [[Liverpool]] in 1868 and migrated to [[Melbourne]] in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], Australia. He came to New Zealand in 1897, where he entered the trade of exporting rabbit skins.<ref name="EP obit">{{cite news |title=Obituary |url= http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&cl=search&d=EP19390105.2.97 |accessdate=12 January 2014 |newspaper=[[The Evening Post (New Zealand)|The Evening Post]] |date=5 January 1939 |volume=CXXVII |issue=3|page=11}}</ref> In 1924, he married [[Helen Black (mayoress)|Helen Black]], who was 30 years his junior.<ref name="DNZB Helen Black">{{DNZB| Tennant| Margaret|authorlink=Margaret Tennant|4b35|Black, Helen McKenzie|10 December 2011}}</ref> Black already had adult sons who were his wife's age, and together they had a further two sons and two daughters.<ref name="DNZB Helen Black" />

He first stood for the Dunedin mayoralty in 1919, but was beaten by [[William Begg]]. He won election in 1929 and served for two terms until the [[Dunedin mayoral election, 1933|1933 election]], when he was beaten by [[Edwin Thomas Cox]].<ref name="EP obit" /><ref name="DNZB Helen Black" /> He stood in the {{NZ election link|1931}} in the {{NZ electorate link|Dunedin North}} electorate as an independent candidate in support of the [[United Party (New Zealand)|United Party]], but withdrew shortly before the election, too late for his name to be removed from the ballot.<ref name="1931 election" >{{cite book |title=The General Election, 1931 |year=1932 |publisher=Government Printer |url= http://atojs.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/atojs?a=d&d=AJHR1932-I-II.2.3.2.31 |page=2 |accessdate=2 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Outlook in Otago |url= http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&cl=search&d=NZH19311130.2.112 |accessdate=11 November 2014 |work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LXVIII |issue=21043 |date=30 November 1931 |page=11}}</ref>

He died in [[Dunedin]] on 4 January 1939.<ref name="EP obit" />

