{{Orphan|date=August 2014}}
'''Yi Xiqun''' ([[Simplified Chinese]]: 衣锡群) (born 1947) is a Chinese entrepreneur.
From 1986 to 1987, Mr. Yi was in charge of the Beijing Municipal Government Economic Structure Reform Committee, and from 1987 to 1991, he was Head of the [[Xicheng District]] in Beijing.<ref>[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=8421580&capId=107597031&previousCapId=3669627&previousTitle=SOHO%20CHINA%20LTD Asian Capital Holdings Ltd (8295:Stock Exchange Of Hong Kong Limited)]</ref> He has served as the Chairman of [[Beijing Enterprises|Beijing Enterprises Holdings]], Assistant to the Mayor of Beijing and Director of the Economic and Foreign Trade Commission of Beijing Municipality and the Management Committee of the [[Beijing Economic and Technological Development Area|Beijing Economic and Technology Development Area]]. He joined the Beijing Enterprises Holdings in 1999.<ref>[http://www.sohochina.com/en/ir#Board-Senior-Management Soho China Ltd (410:Stock Exchange Of Hong Kong Limited)]</ref> He was eventually appointed as Chairman of Beijing Enterprises Holdings in 2003.<ref>[http://www.behl.com.hk/eng/ir/announcements/a030529.pdf Yi Xiqun appointed Chairman of Beijing Enterprises Holdings]</ref> Under his leadership as Chairman, Beijing Enterprises Holdings underwent a large-scale restructuring and successful turnaround from 2003-2009. During those years, the stock returned 32.3% per annum (33.7% including dividends), driven by operational improvements, bolt-on acquisitions and sale of non-core assets. He has been an Independent Non-Executive Director of [[SOHO China]], since 2007, an Independent Non-Executive Director at [http://www.asiancapital.com.hk/ Asian Capital Holdings] since 2010, and Independent Non-Executive Director of [[Industrial and Commercial Bank of China]] since 2013 and has previously served as an Independent Director of [[China Merchants Bank]].<ref>[http://www.icbc-ltd.com/ICBCLtd/Corporate%20Governance/Board%20of%20Directors/Board%20of%20Directors/yixiqun.htm ICBC Profile of Yi Xiqun]</ref> He serves as Executive Vice-Chairman of [http://www.chinacape.org/en/ China Association of Private Equity],<ref>[http://www.chinacape.org/en/index.php?a=aboutlist&id=350 CAPE Committees and Council]</ref> 1st Interim Chairman and Vice President of [http://en.bpea.net.cn/ Beijing Private Equity Association], Vice President of China Association for the Promotion of Industrial Development, and President of Capital Enterprises Association.<ref>[http://en.bpea.net.cn/article/PEPeople/201003/20100300000403.shtml BPEA Biography of Yi Xiqun]</ref> He is a graduate of [[Tsinghua University]].<ref>[http://www.icbc-ltd.com/SiteCollectionDocuments/ICBC/Resources/ICBCLTD/download/2013/wenrenE.pdf Proposed ICBC Appointments]</ref>
